<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="80" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[816,1429,396,559]" box="[816,1019,396,422]" pageId="10" pageNumber="80">
<emphasis box="[816,1019,396,422]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="80">Ecological Notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[816,1429,396,559]" pageId="10" pageNumber="80">
Widespread in caves in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1296,1369,431,457]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="80">China</collectingCountry>
, but never abundant. Maximum count was 24 bats in one cave in 
<collectingRegion box="[912,1001,499,525]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="10" pageNumber="80">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
. An abandoned brick kiln was used by a solitary male in Xinyi County.
</paragraph>
